properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant snowfall is expected. Total snowfall: 10 to 20 cm. Locations: eastern Newfoundland. Time span: Wednesday evening until early Thursday morning. Remarks: Light rain is expected to develop and change over to snow Wednesday evening. The snow may change over to an extended period of freezing rain overnight Wednesday in the Clarenville, Bonavista Peninsula, and Terra Nova regions but at this time there is some uncertainty on how extensive the freezing rain will be. Conditions are expected to improve early Thursday morning. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.
